abstract: Dissenting Democrats may be biggest obstacle to several of Pres Obama's objectives, including expansive trade legislation, authorization to fight Islamic State and nuclear agreement with Iran; while Democrats are largely in agreement on economic issues, they have historically divided on trade and national security.
lead_paragraph: President Obama is finding that his biggest difficulties in pushing his agenda in Congress lately are not with Republicans but with members of his own party.

headline.main: More Democrats Are Going Their Own Way, and That’s Away From Obama
